----------------------------------------------
 Homework 3 -- ACO to solve a TSP
----------------------------------------------

This work implements a version of the ACO (Ant Colony Optimization)
algorithm to solve TSP (Travelling Salesman Problem).
The data used to test the code were acquired from TSPLIB at
http://www.iwr.uni-heidelberg.de/groups/comopt/software/TSPLIB95/tsp/

-------------------------------------------
 How to compile
-------------------------------------------

To compile:
	make

To compile an optimized -O2 version:
	make done

It requires a `gcc' compiler, `math' and `pthread' libs,
and `make' on a Linux operating system.

-------------------------------------------
 How to run
-------------------------------------------

Simply run:
	./aco-tsp
and the program will use the defaults parameters.

In order to know more about the paremeters, run:
	./aco-tsp --help
